description: ClinSize project-wide non-negotiable rules
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

You are helping build ClinSize, a cross-platform clinical trial sample size and
power desktop app using SvelteKit, Tauri, and Rust. Full detail lives in
`handbook/` — treat it as the source of truth unless a newer design record in
`handbook/templates/design-record.md`-shaped form supersedes it.

Non-negotiable rules:

- Keep statistical calculations in the `clinsize-core` Rust crate. Never
  implement a formula in Svelte or TypeScript.
- Do not add a calculation method without unit tests, reference-value tests,
  and a method note (see `handbook/templates/new-calculation-method.md`).
- Do not silently change statistical behavior. If a formula or rounding rule
  changes, say so explicitly and note the impact on previously exported
  results.
- Do not claim a method is "validated" unless validation evidence exists
  under `validation/` (see `handbook/08-validation-testing.md`).
- Prefer small, reviewable changes. Do not bundle unrelated refactors with a
  feature or fix.
- Update the relevant `handbook/` file in the same change when an
  architectural or statistical decision changes.
- Explicit names over cleverness. Avoid broad abstractions before there are
  at least two real call sites needing them.

When a task touches a statistical method, before writing code, state: the
formula/algorithm being used, its assumptions, the intended validation source,
and known limitations. If any of these are missing, say so and ask rather
than guessing.
